White House communications directorJohn Koehler resigned after just one week in the job, sayingPresident Reagans' new chief of staff Howard Baker had a rightto appoint his own team.    Koehler was hired to replace Patrick Buchanan as Reagan'scommunications chief a few days before Donald Regan quit as thepresident's top aide.    "I don't feel I've been jerked around ... I recognize thatSenator Baker must have people around him for the next 22months that he's known for a long time, that he understands,that he's comfortable with and who are comfortable with him,"said Koehler during an appearance in the White House pressroom. Reuter&#3;